Review_body:
I don't expect much out of old 1980's comedies - too often the humor is stupid 'slapstick' or mean-spirited and dated. However, 'Uncle Buck' (1989) is the real deal - a comedy that holds up over time with many laugh-out-loud moments. The cast is full of gems that would go on to be big stars, like Macaulay Culkin and Laurie Metcalf. John Candy is really good in his role.This movie has a current IMDB rating of 7, which is ridiculous (we always glorify the work of comedians and actors that die early in life). But, this is a comedy that does it's job - it made me laugh. A solid 5, and a good comedy.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
